Selection Statements: one of three control flow statements ,
                       known as tools essential for determining order and condition in which code
                       is executed.
                       used for: decision making, repetition, branching

 If Statements: making decision based on specific criteria, conditional control statements
                - Single-If: one possible output (checks a condition/ boolean expression)
                   -> if(condition) {//statement}
                - if .... else: 2 possible outputs (checks 2 conditions and either one will be executed)
                    -> if (condition){//statements
                        }else {
                        //statement
                        }
                   ==> condition true if block executed
                - Multi Branch If: 3+ several outputs
                    -> else if clauses
                    -> if (condition){//statement
                    }else if (condition){
                    }esle{
                    //statement
                    }
                - Nested If: pre conditions for any possible output
                    -> one if statement declared in another one
                    -> whenever one if condition needs to depend on another
                    -> any outer and inner inner if
                - if (condition){
                    if (condition){
                        statement
                        }else if (condition){
                        statement
                        }else {
                        statement
                        }
                       }
