 Switch Statements: - executes statement based on value of variable
                    - executes only one statement from multiple conditions
                    - no boolean expressions only : byte, short, int, ca´har, String, enum
                    - only literals and constants (final values), no variables
                    - value has to be unique
                    - no curly braces for blocks
                    - exiting switch case by using break keyword

                   switch (expression){
                   case constant1:
                    statement 1;
                    statement 2;
                    ...
                    break;
                   case constant1:
                    statement 1;
                    statement 2;
                    ...
                    break;
                   defualt:
                    statement 1;
                    statement 2;
                    ...
                    break;
                    }
