Ternary operator: simplified if statement (shorthand if-else)
                   returns 1 of 2+ values
                   -> (condition)       ?           expression1             :           expression2
                  Ternary condition   if keyword    return value if block   else keyword    return value else block
                   ==> if expression1 is true it will be executed
                   ==> if expression1 is false expression2 will be returned
                   =====>> ? & : must have equal num

